# Project Overview

Boilerplate for mastering AI-assisted development — Cursor AI, Claude Code, MCP servers, agent skills, and swarm orchestration. Initial implementation: Tic-Tac-Toe game.

**Stack:**
- Backend: Python 3.14 + FastAPI + SQLite
- Frontend: Next.js + GPU-accelerated 3D libs, cyberpunk design, mobile-first
- Infrastructure: Docker + Docker Compose, gRPC-Web (Next.js client ↔ Python server)

**Planned structure:**
```
/backend        # FastAPI app
/frontend       # Next.js app
/docker         # Dockerfiles and docker-compose.yml
/.agents/rules/ # Shared rules (symlinked to .claude/rules and .cursor/rules)
/skills/        # Agent skills
/mcp-servers/   # MCP server implementations
```

# Rules

- Do not commit or push unless explicitly instructed (`add . commit`)
- Follow SOLID principles
- Do not break existing functionality — refactor safely
- No unnecessary comments; code should be self-explanatory
- English only in code and comments
- Prioritize security and performance
- Use modern Python 3.14 features

# Communication

- Be terse and direct
- Give the answer immediately — no high-level guidance
- Treat the developer as an expert
- Suggest unconventional solutions when relevant; flag speculation explicitly

# Pre-commit Hooks (planned)

- Claude bot code review
- Strict linter enforcement
